---Note---
This program is an implementation of the compression algorithm LCA, 
implemented by Shirou Maruyama (shirou.maruyama@gmail.com).
The detail is described in our paper ([S.Maruyama et al., "An Online Algorithm for Lightweight Grammar-Based Compression", In proc. of CCP2011, pp19-28]).
This algorithm is not ESP.

Compression Process:
[TEXT] --txt2enc--> [ENCODED CFG] or
[TEXT] --txt2cfg--> [CFG] --cfg2enc--> [ENCODED CFG].

Decompression Process:
[ENCODED CFG] --enc2txt--> [TEXT].
[CFG] --cfg2txt--> [TEXT].


---Algorithms---
LCA-online:  online type grammar-transform algorithm (Recommnended).
LCA-offline: offline type grammar-transform algorithm.

Running time:
LCA-offline > LCA-online.

Space efficiency for main memory:
LCA-online >> LCA-offline.

Compression ratio:
LCA-online = LCA-offline


---Programs & Usage---
"lcacomp" is a standard program.
ex.) %./lcacomp (c|d) <input_file> <output_file>.
   c = Compresses <input_file> with LCA-online and creates <output_file>.
   d = Decompresses <input_file> and creates <output_file>.

"txt2cfg_(online|offline)" transforms an input text into a CFG.
ex.) %./txt2cfg_(online|offline) <TXT_FILE> <CFG_FILE>

"cfg2txt" restores a CFG into the original text.
ex.) %./cfg2txt <CFG_FILE> <TXT_FILE>

"cfg2enc" encodes a CFG by the parentheses encoding.
ex.) %./cfg2enc <CFG_FILE> <ENC_FILE>

"txt2enc_(online|offline)" is a combination of "txt2cfg_(online|offline)" and "cfg2enc".
ex.) %./txt2enc_(online|offline) <TXT_FILE> <ENC_FILE>

"enc2txt" restores an encoded CFG into an original text.
ex.) %./enc2txt <ENC_FILE> <TXT_FILE>
